        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Returns the real valued "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "-point inverse discrete Fourier transform\nof "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", where "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " contains the non-negative frequency terms of a\nHermitian-symmetric sequence. "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the length of the result, not the\ninput."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If you specify an "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " such that "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " must be zero-padded or truncated, the\nextra/removed values will be added/removed at high frequencies. One can\nthus resample a series to "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "m"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " points via Fourier interpolation by:\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "a_resamp = irfft(rfft(a), m)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The correct interpretation of the hermitian input depends on the length of\nthe original data, as given by "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". This is because each input shape could\ncorrespond to either an odd or even length signal. By default, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "irfft"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nassumes an even output length which puts the last entry at the Nyquist\nfrequency; aliasing with its symmetric counterpart. By Hermitian symmetry,\nthe value is thus treated as purely real. To avoid losing information, the\ncorrect length of the real input "
              },
              {
                "kind": "strong",
                "text": "must"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " be given."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.fft.ifft([1, -1j, -1, 1j])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([0.+0.j,  1.+0.j,  0.+0.j,  0.+0.j]) # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.fft.irfft([1, -1j, -1])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([0.,  1.,  0.,  0.])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Notice how the last term in the input to the ordinary "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ifft"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is the\ncomplex conjugate of the second term, and the output has zero imaginary\npart everywhere.  When calling "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "irfft"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", the negative frequencies are not\nspecified, and the output array is purely real."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
